annotationA: Anaphase Promoting Complex subunit 7 (Apc7) associates with the anaphase promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C). It shows synergistic genetic interaction with the essential APC/C subunit, Cdc23. Apc7-APC/C association may be either transient or occurs only in certain forms of the APC/C complex
annotationB: Cell division control protein; Cdc6 is an essential component of the pre-Replication complex (preRC) together with the origin recognition complex, dup and MCM2-7 proteins. The preRC is present at all chromosomal origins of replication and is required for the initiation of DNA replication. Cdc6 also functions in the co-ordination of DNA replication with mitosis, and may contribute to apoptosis and transcription
